    "what_description": "Senna benitoensis is a perennial plant that belongs to the family Fabaceae. It is characterized by its small, yellow flowers that are arranged in axillary racemes, and its flat, elliptical leaflets that are 5-10 cm long and have a crenate margin. The plant grows up to 1.5 meters in height, with a woody base and a spiny stem. The leaves are compound, with 4-8 pairs of leaflets, and are glabrous on the upper surface but pubescent on the lower surface. Senna benitoensis is native to the Baja California Peninsula in Mexico.",
