    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Senna benitoensis are its antimicrobial effects, which have been attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, that inhibit the growth of various pathogens. Senna benitoensis is also used as a laxative due to its high concentration of anthraquinone glycosides, which stimulate bowel movements and relieve constipation. Additionally, its anti-inflammatory properties have been linked to the presence of volatile oils, such as benitoic acid, that exhibit analgesic and anti-edematous activities, providing relief from pain and swelling. Moreover, the antioxidant capacity of Senna benitoensis, which can be attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, protects against oxidative stress and cell damage. Its diuretic properties, resulting from the action of anthraquinone glycosides, increase urine production and help to eliminate excess fluids from the body.",
